\mt1 Zekaryah
\mt2 (Zechariah)
\is1 Introduction
\ip This document lists the prophecies of Zekaryah (Zechariah) concerning Yerushalem (Jerusalem), and tells about the hoped-for Messiah and the final judgement. It consists of two parts: \bd 1\bd*. \it Chapters 1вҖ“8\it*, Zekaryah's prophecy concerning his revelation about saving Yerushalem, the replacement of the temple and its cleaning so that Yahweh's people become holy, and \bd 2\bd*. \it Chapters 9вҖ“14\it*, the prophecies concerning the hoped-for Messiah and the final judgement.
\ip It's believed that this document was written between 520 and 518 before Yeshua/Jesus (B.C.)
\iot Main components of this document
\io1 Warnings and hope \ior 1:1вҖ“8:23\ior*
\io1 The punishment of Yisrael's enemies \ior 9:1-8\ior*
\io1 The arrival of prosperity and peace \ior 9:9вҖ“14:21\ior*
\rem This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the Open English Translation of the Bible. Please double-check the text in advance before using in public.
\ie
\c 1
\s1 Yisrael urged to turn to Yahweh
\rem /s1 Israel Urged to Repent; Zechariah's commission; A Call to Return to the Lord; The Lord Calls His People to Return to Him
\p
\v 1 In the eighthВҰ376325 monthВҰ376324 of the second yearВҰ376326 of \add the reign of Persian King\add* Dareyavesh \add (DariusВҰ376328)\add*, YahwehВҰ376332 \add вүҲspoke through\add* the prophetВҰ376342 Zekaryah (\add ZechariahВҰ376335,\add* son of Iddo'sВҰ376341 son BerekyahВҰ376338) saying,\x + \xo 1:1: \xt Ezr 4:24вҖ“5:1; 6:14.\x*
\v 2 вҖңYahwehВҰ376346 was very angryВҰ376345 with yourВҰ376349 ancestorsВҰ376349,
\v 3 \add вүҲso\add* tell \add this to\add* \add @the people\add*: Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ376356 says \add вүҲthat if you all turn back\add* to me, I'llВҰ376363 return to you.
\v 4 Don'tВҰ376369 be like your ancestorsВҰ376372 who'd been told by the prophetsВҰ376377 that Commander-in-chief Yahweh wanted them to abandon \add вүҲall\add* their evil practices, \add вүҲbutВҰ376388\add* they wouldn't listenВҰ376393 or pay attentionВҰ376396. That is Yahweh'sВҰ376382 declarationВҰ376398.
\p
\v 5 вҖң\add So\add* whereВҰ376403 are you ancestors andВҰ376406 the prophetsВҰ376406 \add now\add*? Do theyВҰ376405 liveВҰ376408 foreverВҰ376407?
\v 6 ButВҰ376413 yourВҰ376422 ancestorsВҰ376422 \add вүҲdidn'tВҰ376420 obey\add* my wordsВҰ376412 and my decrees thatВҰ376414 IВҰ376415 commandedВҰ376415 \add through\add* my servantsВҰ376418 the prophetsВҰ376419, butВҰ376410 theyВҰ376424 \add eventually\add* repentedВҰ376423 and saidВҰ376424, вҖҳCommander-in-chief YahwehВҰ376427 has doneВҰ376434 to us just what our waysВҰ376431 and actions deserved.вҖҷ вҖқ
\s1 Yahweh's compassion for Yerushalem
\rem /s1 First Vision: The Horsemen; Eight visions with their interpretations; The Man Among the Myrtle Trees; A Man among the Myrtle Trees; The Prophet's Vision of the Horses
\p
\v 7 \add вүҲAbout three months later\add*, YahwehВҰ376455 \add вүҲspoke again through\add* the prophetВҰ376465 Zekaryah (\add ZechariahВҰ376458\add* son of Iddo'sВҰ376464 son BerekyahВҰ376461) saying,
\v 8 вҖңI \add вүҲhad a vision\add* in the nightВҰ376470, and \add вүҲwas surprised to see\add* a manВҰ376473 ridingВҰ376474 onВҰ376484 a red horseВҰ376477,\x + \xo 1:8a: \xt Rev 6:4.\x* and then he was standingВҰ376480 among the myrtleВҰ376482 treesВҰ376482 thatВҰ376483 are in the valley, and behindВҰ376485 him there were red, reddish-brown, and whiteВҰ376489 horsesВҰ376486.вҖқ\x + \xo 1:8b: \xt Rev 6:2.\x*
\v 9 I \add вүҲaskedВҰ376491\add*, вҖңWhat are these things, my masterВҰ376495?вҖқ
\p ThenВҰ376491 \add вүҲthat\add* \add heavenly\add* messengerВҰ376498 who talked withВҰ376500 me told me, вҖңI'llВҰ376502 show youВҰ376502 what those things are.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 ThenВҰ376508 the manВҰ376509 who stood among the myrtleВҰ376513 treesВҰ376513 answeredВҰ376508 andВҰ376515 saidВҰ376515, вҖңThoseВҰ376518 are the ones that YahwehВҰ376519 has sentВҰ376518 out to roam throughout the world.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 They answeredВҰ376523 Yahweh'sВҰ376527 messengerВҰ376526 who stood among the myrtleВҰ376530 treesВҰ376530, telling him, вҖңWe've been roaming throughout the world, and see, the whole world sits \add вүҲcontentedly\add* and is at peaceВҰ376539.вҖқ
\p
\v 12 вҖңCommander-in-chief Yahweh,вҖқ Yahweh'sВҰ376544 messengerВҰ376542 \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖңhow long \add вүҲbefore\add* you show compassionВҰ376554 to YerushalemВҰ376557 andВҰ376541 to the citiesВҰ376559 of YehudahВҰ376560 \add (Judah)\add*, whichВҰ376561 you'veВҰ376554 been angryВҰ376562 with for the past seventyВҰ376564 years?вҖқ
\p
\v 13 ThenВҰ376567 that messengerВҰ376571 who'd talkedВҰ376572 with me was answeredВҰ376567 by YahwehВҰ376568 with kind andВҰ376567 comfortingВҰ376577 words,
\v 14 and that messengerВҰ376581 told me, вҖңCall out and sayВҰ376585, вҖҳCommander-in-chief YahwehВҰ376588 saysВҰ376587 this: I've been \add вүҲvery\add* jealousВҰ376590 for YerushalemВҰ376591 and for TsiyyonВҰ376592 \add (ZionВҰ376592)\add*.
\v 15 I'm very angry with the countriesВҰ376602 that are at easeвҖ”I was only a littleВҰ376607 angry with them, \add вүҲbutВҰ376596\add* they made the disasterВҰ376610 worse.
\v 16 Therefore Yahweh saysВҰ376615: I \add вүҲwill show mercy\add* YerushalemВҰ376618 \add вүҲagain\add*. My residence will be builtВҰ376621 within her, andВҰ376626 the measuringВҰ376626 line will be stretchedВҰ376628 out over her. That's what Commander-in-chief Yahweh declaresВҰ376623.
\p
\v 17 вҖңAgainВҰ376633, call out and sayВҰ376636, вҖҳCommander-in-chief YahwehВҰ376639 saysВҰ376638 this: MyВҰ376646 citiesВҰ376643 will once again overflowВҰ376642 withВҰ376653 goodness, and \add *I\add* will again comfortВҰ376645 TsiyyonВҰ376650 and chooseВҰ376651 YerushalemВҰ376653.вҖҷ вҖқ
\s1 The vision of the four horns
\rem /s1 The Vision of the Horns; Four Horns and Four Blacksmiths; Four Horns and Four Craftsmen; Second Vision: The Horns and the Smiths
\p
\v 18 Then I \add вүҲlooked up\add* and wow, I saw four horns.
\v 19 I \add вүҲasked\add* the messenger who'd talked with me, вҖңWhat are those?вҖқ
\p вҖңThose are the horns that have scattered Yehudah, Yisrael, and Yerushalem.вҖқ he \add вүҲanswered\add*.
\p
\v 20 Then Yahweh showed me four craftsmen
\v 21 and I \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖңWhat are those people coming to do?вҖқ
\p вҖңThose horns are \add the nations\add* that scattered Yehudah so that \add вүҲeveryone went into hiding\add*,вҖқ he \add вүҲanswered\add*, вҖңBut the blacksmiths have come to terrify \add the horns\add*вҖ”to \add вүҲamputate\add* the horns of the nations that \add вүҲattacked\add* Yehudah, scattering \add @the people\add*.вҖқ
\c 2
\s1 The vision of Yerushalem expanded
\rem /s1 Third Vision: The Man with a Measuring Line; A Man With a Measuring Line; The Vision of the Measuring Line; Future Prosperity of Jerusalem
\p
\v 1 Then I \add вүҲlooked up\add*, and wow, I sawВҰ376661 a man \add вүҲholding\add* a measuring line\f + \fr 2:1 \ft The modern equivalent would be a tape measure.\f*
\v 2 and I askedВҰ376667 him, вҖңWhere are you going?вҖқ
\p вҖңTo measure YerushalemВҰ376688,вҖқ he \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңand to determine its width and length.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 ThenВҰ376694 \add вүҲto my surprise\add*, the messenger who'd talked with me went away andВҰ376693 another messenger went out to meet him
\v 4 and told him, вҖңRun and speak to thatВҰ376708 young manВҰ376716, saying: Yerushalem \add вүҲwon'tВҰ376717 need city walls\add* because \add вүҲthere'll be so many\add* people and animals within it.
\v 5 Yahweh declares that he'll become a wall of fire around it and will become the splendour inВҰ376746 the middle of it.
\s1 Yahweh commands the exiles to go home
\rem /s1 The Exiles Are Called Home; Interlude: An Appeal to the Exiles; The Exiles Are Called to Come Home
\p
\v 6 Yahweh declares: Get up \add вүҲand get moving\add*. Flee from that land in the north, because I had scattered youВҰ376753 into the four winds.
\v 7 \add Now\add* run you \add вүҲpeople who live inВҰ376772\add* BabylonвҖ”escape to Tsiyyon \add (Zion)\add*.
\v 8 Commander-in-chief Yahweh saidВҰ376780 that, after he honoured and sent me against the nations that plundered youвҖ”
\q1 becauseВҰ376794 whoever touches you, \add вүҲis messing withВҰ376797 God's favourite\add*.
\p
\v 9 \add He said,\add* вҖңI myself will \add вүҲpunish\add* them, and they'll be \add вүҲlooted by\add* their \add own\add* slaves.вҖқ
\p \add When you see that,\add* then you'll know that Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ376806 sent me.
\p
\v 10 YahwehВҰ376823 declares: вҖңSing and be glad, daughter of Tsiyyon, becauseВҰ376824 I myself will come and settle among youВҰ376829.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 Then powerful nations will join Yahweh \add вүҲat that time\add*, and they will become his people. He will settle among you, and you will know that Commander-in-chief Yahweh has sent me to you.
\v 12 Then YahwehВҰ376848 will inherit Yehudah as his rightful possession inВҰ376860 thatВҰ376856 sacred region, and will once again choose Yerushalem.
\p
\v 13 AllВҰ376867 \add вүҲpeople everywhere\add*, be silent before YahwehВҰ376880, becauseВҰ376866 from his sacred place, he's been driven into action.
\c 3
\s1 Joshua and Satan
\rem /s1 Cleansing for the High Priest; Clean Garments for the High Priest; The Prophet's Vision of the High Priest; Fourth Vision: Joshua and Satan
\p
\v 1 Then Yahweh showedВҰ376950 me the highВҰ376955 priestВҰ376954 Yehoshua \add (Joshua)\add* standing in frontВҰ376957 of Yahweh'sВҰ376959 messengerВҰ376958, and Satan was standing at his rightВҰ376964 to accuseВҰ376965 himВҰ376965.\x + \xo 3:1: a \xt Ezr 5:2; \xo b \xt Rev 12:10.\x*
\v 2 \add вүҲButВҰ376967\add* Yahweh told Satan, вҖңMay Yahweh rebuke you, SatanвҖ”may Yahweh who's chosenВҰ376979 YerushalemВҰ376980, rebuke you. Isn't \add he energetic like\add* a burningВҰ376985 stick taken out of the fireВҰ376985?вҖқ\x + \xo 3:2: \xt Jude 9.\x*
\p
\v 3 Now Yehoshua was dressed in filthyВҰ376991 clothesВҰ376989 as he stoodВҰ376992 in frontВҰ376993 of the messengerВҰ376994
\v 4 \add вүҲwho\add* told thoseВҰ377000 standingВҰ377000 in front of him, вҖңTake off his filthyВҰ377006 clothes.вҖқ
\p ThenВҰ376996 he said to Yehoshua, вҖңListen, I'veВҰ377011 \add вүҲtakenВҰ377011 away the guilt of your disobedience\add*, andВҰ376996 I'llВҰ377014 dress you in nice clothes.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 вҖңLet them put a clean headband on his head,вҖқ I saidВҰ377018, \add вүҲso\add* they placed a clean headband on Yehoshua's head andВҰ377018 dressed him with \add new\add* clothesВҰ377031, while Yahweh'sВҰ377034 messengerВҰ377033 was standingВҰ377035 \add there watching\add*.
\p
\v 6 ThenВҰ377037 \add *he\add* told Yehoshua,
\v 7 вҖңCommander-in-chief YahwehВҰ377046 saysВҰ377045: If you'll \add вүҲfollow my instructions\add* and obey my rules, then you can governВҰ377060 my \add вүҲtemple\add* and guardВҰ377065 my courtyardsВҰ377068, because I'llВҰ377069 allow you to walkВҰ377051 among theseВҰ377074 who are standingВҰ377073 here.
\v 8 Please listen, Yehoshua the highВҰ377082 priestВҰ377081, \add вүҲas well as\add* yourВҰ377086 companionsВҰ377084 sittingВҰ377085 in frontВҰ377086 of youВҰ377083. Those these menВҰ377089 are a signВҰ377090, becauseВҰ377087 I myself will bringВҰ377095 out my servantВҰ377098 вҖҳthe branchВҰ377099вҖҷ.\x + \xo 3:8: \xt Jer 23:5; 33:15; Zech 6:12.\x*
\v 9 Now look at the stone that I'veВҰ377106 placed in frontВҰ377107 of YehoshuaвҖ”a single stone with sevenВҰ377113 \add вүҲfaces\add* \add cut on it\add*. Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ377119 declaresВҰ377118 that I will engraveВҰ377116 an inscriptionВҰ377117 on it, and I will removeВҰ377121 the sin from this land in one dayВҰ377128.
\v 10 Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ377134 declaresВҰ377133 that in that dayВҰ377131, each manВҰ377137 will inviteВҰ377136 his neighbourВҰ377138 to sit under his grapevineВҰ377142 or under his figВҰ377146 treeВҰ377146.вҖқ\x + \xo 3:10: \xt Mic 4:4.\x*
\c 4
\s1 The container of lamp and the two olives
\rem /s1 A Lampstand and Two Olive Trees; The Gold Lampstand and the Two Olive Trees; Fifth Vision: The Lampstand and Olive Trees; The Vision of the Lampstand
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ377148 the messengerВҰ377149 who was talkingВҰ377150 withВҰ377151 me turned andВҰ377152 woke me as if waking someone from their sleepВҰ377157.
\v 2 вҖңWhat do you see?вҖқ he \add вүҲasked\add* me.
\p вҖңWow,вҖқ I said, вҖңI see a lampstand made entirely of goldВҰ377170, with a bowl on top of it. It has seven lamps on the top \add вүҲwith a tube feeding each one\add*,
\v 3 andВҰ377195 twoВҰ377189 oliveВҰ377190 treesВҰ377190 by itвҖ”one on \add вүҲeach side of it\add*.вҖқ\x + \xo 4:3: \xt Rev 11:4.\x*
\v 4 ThenВҰ377200 I askedВҰ377200 the messengerВҰ377204 who was talkingВҰ377205 withВҰ377206 me, вҖңWhat are those, my masterВҰ377211?вҖқ
\p
\v 5 вҖңDon'tВҰ377219 youВҰ377220 knowВҰ377220 what those things mean?вҖқ \add *he\add* \add вүҲasked\add* me.
\p вҖңNo, my masterВҰ377227,вҖқ I \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲSoВҰ377229\add* he told me, вҖңThis is Yahweh'sВҰ377236 messageВҰ377234 to Zerubavel: Commander-in-chief Yahweh saysВҰ377249 it won'tВҰ377241 be my strengthВҰ377242 or my powerВҰ377244, butВҰ377229 withВҰ377242 my spiritВҰ377248.\x + \xo 4:6: \xt Ezr 5:2.\x*
\v 7 What are you, big mountainВҰ377256? Before Zerubavel you will become a plainВҰ377261. Then he will bringВҰ377262 out the top stoneВҰ377265 to shoutsВҰ377267 of вҖҳGrace, grace to it.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 8 Then Yahweh'sВҰ377276 messageВҰ377274 \add came\add* to me, saying,
\v 9 вҖңZerubavel's hands have laid the foundationВҰ377282 of this \add вүҲtemple\add* and his hands will bring it to completion.вҖқ Then you will \add вүҲhave confirmation\add* that Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ377290 has sent me to you.
\v 10 Because who has \add вүҲmocked those who make a smallВҰ377299 difference\add*? They will rejoiceВҰ377300 and will seeВҰ377301 Zerubavel \add вүҲholding a plumbВҰ377304 line\add*.
\p Those sevenВҰ377308 \add lamps\add* are Yahweh'sВҰ377312 eyesВҰ377311 that roam over the whole world.
\p
\v 11 вҖңWhat are theseВҰ377326 twoВҰ377324 oliveВҰ377325 treesВҰ377325 on the rightВҰ377329 andВҰ377319 left of the lampstandВҰ377330?вҖқ I \add вүҲasked\add* the messenger.\x + \xo 4:11: \xt Rev 11:4.\x*
\v 12 вҖңAnd what are these two oliveВҰ377343 branches besideВҰ377345 the two gold pipesВҰ377347 thatВҰ377344 have goldenВҰ377348 oil pouringВҰ377349 out of them?вҖқ
\p
\v 13 ThenВҰ377353 he \add вүҲanswered\add*, вҖңDon'tВҰ377356 youВҰ377357 knowВҰ377357 what those are?вҖқ
\p вҖңNo, my masterВҰ377363,вҖқ I \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\p
\v 14 ThenВҰ377365 he saidВҰ377365, вҖңThose are the twoВҰ377367 \add вүҲanointedВҰ377370 men\add*\f + \fr 4:14 \ft It's not clear who this is referring to.\f* who standВҰ377371 before the masterВҰ377374 of the whole world.вҖқ
\c 5
\s1 The flying scroll vision
\rem /s1 The Flying Scroll; Sixth Vision: The Flying Scroll; The Vision of the Flying Scroll; A Flying Scroll
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ377379 I turned around and \add вүҲlooked up\add*, and wow, I sawВҰ377382 a flyingВҰ377385 scrollВҰ377384,
\v 2 and \add @the messenger\add* \add вүҲasked\add* me, вҖңWhat do youВҰ377390 see?вҖқ
\p вҖңI see a flyingВҰ377396 scrollВҰ377395,вҖқ I answeredВҰ377392, вҖңthat's nine metresВҰ377399 longВҰ377397 and \add вүҲhalf that\add* wideВҰ377400.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 ThenВҰ377404 he told me, вҖңThat's the curseВҰ377407 thatВҰ377408 goes out over the surfaceВҰ377411 of the whole land. Every thief will be removed according to what it says on the one side, andВҰ377404 everyoneВҰ377416 who \add вүҲtestifies falsely\add* will be removed according to what it says on the otherВҰ377425 side.
\v 4 Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ377431 declares: I will send it out so it will enterВҰ377433 into the house of \add вүҲany\add* thiefВҰ377437 and into the house of anyoneВҰ377441 who \add вүҲtestified falselyВҰ377443 using\add* my name, and it will remain inВҰ377442 that house and \add вүҲeat away atВҰ377442\add* its timberВҰ377450 and its stonesВҰ377453.вҖқ
\s1 The woman in a basket vision
\rem /s1 The Woman in a Basket; Seventh Vision: The Woman in a Basket; The Vision of the Woman in the Basket; A Woman in a Basket
\p
\v 5 ThenВҰ377455 the messengerВҰ377456 who'd been talkingВҰ377457 withВҰ377458 me \add вүҲcame over\add* and saidВҰ377459 to me, вҖң\add вүҲLook up\add* and seeВҰ377464 what's coming now.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 вҖңWhat is it?вҖқ I \add вүҲaskedВҰ377469\add*.
\p And he said, вҖңThat's the measuring binВҰ377475 that's coming.вҖқ ThenВҰ377469 he \add вүҲcontinuedВҰ377473\add*, вҖңThat's theirВҰ377479 eyeВҰ377479\f + \fr 5:6 \ft Some ancient translations have вҖҳiniquityвҖҷ here, but we've stayed with the Hebrew.\f* across the whole land.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 ThenВҰ377484, wow, a lead coveringВҰ377485 was lifted off andВҰ377488 there was a womanВҰ377489 sittingВҰ377491 inside the measuring bin.
\v 8 He saidВҰ377495, вҖңThis \add >woman\add* is вҖҳwickednessВҰ377497вҖҷ.вҖқ ThenВҰ377495 he \add вүҲpushed\add* her \add back\add* inside the measuring bin, thenВҰ377495 \add quickly\add* pressedВҰ377504 the \add вүҲheavy\add* lead \add cover back\add* over its opening.
\p
\v 9 Then I \add вүҲlooked up\add* \add again\add* and wow, I sawВҰ377516 twoВҰ377518 womenВҰ377519 withВҰ377522 wings like stork'sВҰ377526 wings, flying onВҰ377522 the wind towards us, and theyВҰ377523 lifted the measuring bin up \add вүҲinto\add* the sky.
\p
\v 10 вҖңWhere are theyВҰ377543 takingВҰ377544 the measuring bin?вҖқ I askedВҰ377536 the messengerВҰ377539 who'd been talkingВҰ377540 withВҰ377541 me.
\p
\v 11 вҖңTo buildВҰ377551 a temple for it in \add вүҲBabylonia\add*,вҖқ he \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖңAnd when it's ready, it'll be set on a base thereВҰ377559.вҖқ
\c 6
\s1 The four chariots vision
\rem /s1 The Vision of the Four Chariots; Four Chariots; Eighth Vision: Four Chariots
\p
\v 1 Then I turned and \add вүҲlooked up\add* and wow, I sawВҰ377568 fourВҰ377570 chariotsВҰ377571 comingВҰ377572 out from betweenВҰ377573 twoВҰ377574 bronzeВҰ377578 mountains.
\v 2 The firstВҰ377581 chariot \add was being pulled by\add* red horses, the secondВҰ377585 by blackВҰ377587 horses,\x + \xo 6:2: a \xt Rev 6:4; \xo b \xt Rev 6:5.\x*
\v 3 the thirdВҰ377590 by whiteВҰ377592 horses, andВҰ377589 the fourthВҰ377594 by \add вүҲspotted gray\add* horses.\x + \xo 6:3: \xt Rev 6:2.\x*
\p
\v 4 I \add вүҲasked\add* the messengerВҰ377603 who had talked withВҰ377605 me, вҖңWhat are those, my masterВҰ377609?вҖқ
\v 5 вҖңThose are fourВҰ377616 windsВҰ377617 of the heavensВҰ377618 thatВҰ377619 goВҰ377619 out from where they were, ahead of the masterВҰ377623 of the whole world,вҖқ he answeredВҰ377611.\x + \xo 6:5: \xt Rev 7:1.\x*
