\s1 The two shepherds
\rem /s1 The Two Shepherds; The Good and Evil Shepherds; Two Shepherds; Two Kinds of Shepherds
\p
\v 4 My godВҰ378981 YahwehВҰ378980 saysВҰ378979: вҖңBe like a shepherdВҰ378982 who's watching over the flockВҰ378985 \add вүҲthat have been marked to be slaughteredВҰ378986\add*.
\v 5 The ones who buy them, slaughterВҰ378990 them and aren'tВҰ378991 punished, and the ones who sell them sayВҰ378994, вҖҳBlessed be YahwehВҰ378996. I've becomeВҰ378997 rich.вҖҷ because the shepherdsВҰ378998 working for the flocks' owners have no pity on them.
\p
\v 6 This is Yahweh'sВҰ379013 declaration: I will no longer \add вүҲfeel sorry for the people of this country\add*. Listen, I'm aboutВҰ379016 to \add вүҲallow everyone to be taken over\add* by \add #their neighboursВҰ379023\add* and by \add #their kingВҰ379025\add* and \add allow them to\add* destroy the land, and I \add вүҲwon'tВҰ379004 rescueВҰ379016 anyone from them\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 SoВҰ379034 I became the shepherd of the flock that had been marked for slaughterВҰ379038вҖ”the ones who were suffering the most. I tookВҰ379042 twoВҰ379045 \add shepherd's\add* staffsВҰ379046вҖ”I named one вҖҳFavourвҖҷ, and the otherВҰ379050 I named вҖҳUnityвҖҷ, and thenВҰ379034 I shepherded the flock.
\v 8 ThenВҰ379058 I destroyed the threeВҰ379061 shepherdsВҰ379062вҖ”inВҰ379063 one monthВҰ379063 I became impatientВҰ379065 withВҰ379063 them, andВҰ379058 they also hated me.
\v 9 \add вүҲSoВҰ379074\add* I saidВҰ379074 to the owners, вҖңI won'tВҰ379075 work for youВҰ379077 any longer as a shepherdВҰ379076. The sheep that are dyingВҰ379078вҖ”let them dieВҰ379079. The sheep that are beingВҰ379080 destroyedвҖ”let them be destroyed. Let the sheep that remain \add вүҲstart eating each other\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 ThenВҰ379090 I tookВҰ379090 my staffВҰ379093 \add named\add* вҖҳFavourвҖҷ andВҰ379097 brokeВҰ379097 it to breakВҰ379099 the agreementВҰ379102 thatВҰ379103 I'd made with \add вүҲall of my tribes\add*.
\v 11 \add вүҲSoВҰ379111\add* the agreement was brokenВҰ379111 on that dayВҰ379112, and the ones in the flockВҰ379117 who were suffering the most and who were watchingВҰ379118 me, knewВҰ379114 that YahwehВҰ379123 had spoken.
\v 12 ThenВҰ379126 I told them, вҖңIf itВҰ379130 seems goodВҰ379130 to youВҰ379131, \add вүҲgiveВҰ379132\add* me my wages, butВҰ379126 if not, don'tВҰ379136 \add вүҲbother\add*.вҖқ SoВҰ379126 theyВҰ379139 \add вүҲpaid me thirtyВҰ379143 silverВҰ379144 coins\add*.\x + \xo 11:12-13: \xt Mat 27:9-10.\x*
\p
\v 13 ThenВҰ379146 Yahweh told me, вҖңGive the \add вүҲmoney\add* to the potter\f + \fr 11:13 \ft potter (following the Hebrew): in the ancient Syriac translation, they used вҖҳtreasuryвҖҷ (2x) in this verse, so some other English translations might differ.\f*вҖ”the \add вүҲpathetic amount thatВҰ379155 they valuedВҰ379156 you at\add*.вҖқ SoВҰ379146 I tookВҰ379158 the thirtyВҰ379159 silverВҰ379160 \add вүҲcoins\add* andВҰ379146 tossed them to the potter in Yahweh'sВҰ379147 \add вүҲtemple\add*.
\v 14 ThenВҰ379169 I brokeВҰ379169 my secondВҰ379173 staffВҰ379172 \add named\add* вҖҳUnityвҖҷ to breakВҰ379176 the brotherhoodВҰ379179 between YehudahВҰ379181 andВҰ379182 YisraelВҰ379183.
\p
\v 15 \add вүҲAfter that,\add* YahwehВҰ379187 told me, вҖңAgain, takeВҰ379190 the equipmentВҰ379193 of a \add вүҲsimple\add* shepherdВҰ379194 for yourselfВҰ379192,
\v 16 because listen, I'm aboutВҰ379201 to set a shepherdВҰ379202 in place in the land who won't care for \add вүҲthoseВҰ379204 who are dying\add*. He won't seek out the sheep gone missing, nor will he healВҰ379214 the crippled sheep. He won't feed the sheep thatВҰ379204 are healthyВҰ379215, butВҰ379212 he'll tear off the hoovesВҰ379221 of the fattened sheep and \add вүҲeatВҰ379220 them for meatВҰ379218\add*.
\q1
\v 17 The worthlessВҰ379227 shepherdВҰ379226 who abandonsВҰ379228 the flockВҰ379229 \add вүҲwon't end well\add*.
\q1 May the swordВҰ379230 come against his arm and his right eye.
\q1 вүҲMay his arm wither away and may his right eye become blind.вҖқ
\c 12
\s1 Yerushalem's protection
\rem /s1 Jerusalem a centre of worship for all; Future Deliverance for Jerusalem; Jerusalem's Enemies to Be Destroyed; Jerusalem's Victory; The Future Deliverance of Jerusalem
\rem /s2 An Oracle
\rem /d
\p
\v 1 This is a declaration of Yahweh'sВҰ379250 messageВҰ379248 concerning YisraelВҰ379253вҖ”a declaration of Yahweh, who stretchedВҰ379257 out the skies and laid the foundationВҰ379259 of the earthВҰ379260, who formsВҰ379261 the humanВҰ379264 spiritВҰ379262 \add вүҲthat's inside people\add*,
\v 2 вҖңListen, I'm aboutВҰ379270 to make Yerushalem into a cup causing all the nations surrounding her to stagger aroundВҰ379280. It will also be like that for YehudahВҰ379284 during the siegeВҰ379286 against Yerushalem.
\v 3 \add вүҲAt that time\add*, I'llВҰ379295 make YerushalemВҰ379298 into a heavy stone for all the peoplesВҰ379303. Anyone trying to lift that stone will hurt himself very much, andВҰ379291 all the nationsВҰ379312 inВҰ379292 the world will gatherВҰ379309 against that city.
\v 4 This is Yahweh'sВҰ379319 declaration: \add вүҲAt that time\add*, I will strike every horse with confusion and its riderВҰ379325 with madnessВҰ379326. I'll open my eyesВҰ379334 over the YehudahВҰ379330 \add вүҲregion\add*, butВҰ379325 I'll strike every horse \add вүҲfrom other countries\add* with blindnessВҰ379339.
\v 5 ThenВҰ379341 the leaders of YehudahВҰ379343 will \add вүҲsayВҰ379341 to themselvesВҰ379344\add*, вҖҳThe inhabitantsВҰ379347 of YerushalemВҰ379348 are our strengthВҰ379345 because of their godВҰ379351, Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ379349.вҖҷ
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲAt that time\add*, I will make the leaders of YehudahВҰ379359 like firepots among wood and like a flaming torchВҰ379363 among standing grainВҰ379365, because they'll devour all the surrounding peoplesВҰ379377 on their rightВҰ379369 and on their left. YerushalemВҰ379380 will againВҰ379381 live inВҰ379362 her own placeВҰ379382.вҖқ
\s1 Saving Yerushalem's inhabitants
\p
\v 7 YahwehВҰ379387 will saveВҰ379386 Yehudah'sВҰ379391 tentsВҰ379390 firstВҰ379392, so that the honour of David'sВҰ379400 \add вүҲdescendants\add* and the honour of Yerushalem'sВҰ379403 inhabitantsВҰ379402 won'tВҰ379394 be greaterВҰ379396 than the rest of Yehudah.
\v 8 \add вүҲAt that time\add*, Yahweh will be the defenderВҰ379410 of the inhabitantsВҰ379413 of YerushalemВҰ379414. Those among them who are weak will \add вүҲbecome\add* \add strong\add* like David, while the David'sВҰ379420 \add вүҲdescendants\add* will be like God, like Yahweh'sВҰ379411 messengerВҰ379424 \add вүҲgoing ahead\add* of them.
\v 9 вҖңOn that dayВҰ379429 I will begin to destroyВҰ379432 all the nationsВҰ379437 that \add вүҲfight\add* against YerushalemВҰ379441.вҖқ
\rem /s1 Mourning for the One They Pierced; Mourning for the Pierced One
\p
\v 10 ButВҰ379443 I will pour out a spiritВҰ379452 of compassion and pleading on David'sВҰ379447 \add вүҲdescendants\add* and the inhabitantsВҰ379450 of YerushalemВҰ379451, so they will lookВҰ379455 on meвҖ”the one they've piercedВҰ379460. They'll mourn for me, as one mourns for an only sonвҖ”they will wail bitterlyВҰ379467 for him like those who wail after the death of a firstbornВҰ379472 son.\x + \xo 12:10: \xt Yhn 19:37; Rev 1:7.\x*
\v 11 On that dayВҰ379474 the wailing in YerushalemВҰ379478 will be like the wailing atВҰ379478 HadadВҰ379480-RimmonВҰ379482 in the MegiddoВҰ379484 plainВҰ379483.
\v 12 The land will mournВҰ379486, each clan separate from other clans. The clan of David'sВҰ379494 \add вүҲdescendants\add* will be separate and their wives will be separate from the men. The clan of Nathan'sВҰ379501 \add вүҲdescendants\add* will be separate and their wives will \add also\add* be separate from the men.
\v 13 The clan of Levi'sВҰ379509 \add вүҲdescendants\add* will be separate and their wives will be separate from the men. The clan of the Shimeites will be separate and their wives will \add also\add* be separate from the men.
\v 14 Each of the remainingВҰ379521 clans will be separate andВҰ379525 the wivesВҰ379525 will be separate from the men.вҖқ
\c 13
\s1 The cleaning of sins from Yisrael
\rem /s1 A Fountain of Cleansing; Cleansing From Sin
\p
\v 1 вҖңOn that dayВҰ379529 a spring will be openedВҰ379533 for David'sВҰ379535 \add вүҲdescendants\add* and the \add other\add* inhabitantsВҰ379536 of YerushalemВҰ379537, \add to clean them from\add* their sinВҰ379538 and impurityВҰ379539.
\rem /s1 Idolatry Cut Off
\p
\v 2 This is the declaration of Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ379546: That \add same\add* dayВҰ379542, I will \add вүҲeliminate\add* the namesВҰ379551 of the idolsВҰ379552 from the \add вүҲcountry\add* and \add вүҲthenВҰ379541 no one will be able to rememberВҰ379557 them\add*. I'llВҰ379548 remove the \add false\add* prophetsВҰ379562 and the spiritВҰ379565 of impurity from the land.
\v 3 If anyoneВҰ379576 continues to prophesy, hisВҰ379582 father and mother will tell him, вҖҳYou \add вүҲcan'tВҰ379583 be allowed to\add* live becauseВҰ379573 you speak lies \add вүҲusing\add* Yahweh'sВҰ379589 nameвҖҷ ThenВҰ379572 the \add very\add* father and mother who \add вүҲgave birth to\add* him will \add вүҲrun him throughВҰ379590\add* when he prophesies.
\v 4 \add вүҲAt that time\add*, each prophet will become ashamedВҰ379600 of his visionВҰ379603 when he is about to prophesy, \add so\add* inВҰ379604 order to deceiveВҰ379610 \add the people\add*, these prophets won'tВҰ379605 put onВҰ379604 a hairy cloakВҰ379607 any more,
\v 5 andВҰ379612 they'll \add each\add* say, вҖҳI'm not a prophetВҰ379614. I'm a manВҰ379616 who works the soilвҖ”\add вүҲI've been doing that sinceВҰ379624 I was\add* young.вҖҷ
\v 6 \add вүҲButВҰ379626\add* \add someone\add* will \add вүҲask\add* him, вҖҳWhat are theseВҰ379630 wounds betweenВҰ379631 yourВҰ379632 arms?вҖҷ andВҰ379633 he'll \add вүҲanswer\add*, вҖҳI got \add accidentally\add* woundedВҰ379635 in my friends' houseВҰ379636.вҖҷ вҖқ
\s1 The shepherd gets attacked
\rem /s1 The Scattering of the Sheep; The Shepherd Struck, the Sheep Scattered; The Shepherd Struck, the Flock Scattered; The Command to Kill God's Shepherd
\p
\v 7 ArmyВҰ379651 command YahwehВҰ379650 declares:
\q1 Wake up, swordВҰ379640, \add and work\add* against \add the one who's\add* my shepherd and the manВҰ379647 who stands close to me.
\q1 Strike the shepherd and the flock will scatterВҰ379656
\q1 because I'llВҰ379658 turn my handВҰ379659 against the lowly \add >ones\add*.\x + \xo 13:7: \xt Mat 26:31; Mrk 14:27.\x*
\q1
\v 8 YahwehВҰ379670 declares: ThenВҰ379664 it'll come about that throughout all the land,
\q1 that two-thirds of it will be cut off.
\q1 Those people will \add вүҲdie\add*вҖ”only one-third will remain there.
\q1
\v 9 I'll bringВҰ379681 that thirdВҰ379684 through the fireВҰ379685 and refine them like silverВҰ379690 is refined.
\q1 вүҲI'll test them like goldВҰ379695 is testedВҰ379692.
\q1 They will call \add вүҲout to me for help\add*,
\q1 and I'll answerВҰ379701 them saying, вҖҳThis is my peopleВҰ379704.вҖҷ
\q1 and they'll say, вҖҳYahwehВҰ379708 is my godВҰ379709.вҖҷ вҖқ
\c 14
\s1 God appears and reigns
\rem /s1 Jerusalem and the Nations; The Lord Will Rule the Earth; Future Warfare and Final Victory; The Lord Comes and Reigns
\p
\v 1 Listen, a dayВҰ379713 is comingВҰ379715 for YahwehВҰ379716, when yourВҰ379719 plunderВҰ379718 will be dividedВҰ379717 \add вүҲright inВҰ379719 front of youВҰ379718\add*,
\v 2 because I will assemble every country to battleВҰ379731 against YerushalemВҰ379730 and the city will be capturedВҰ379732. The housesВҰ379735 will be plunderedВҰ379734 and the womenВҰ379736 raped. Half of the city will \add вүҲbe led away\add* into captivity, butВҰ379721 the remainder of the peopleВҰ379744 won'tВҰ379745 be \add вүҲevicted\add* from the city.
\v 3 ThenВҰ379751 YahwehВҰ379752 will goВҰ379751 out andВҰ379751 fight againstВҰ379754 thoseВҰ379755 nationsВҰ379754 like when he fights onВҰ379754 the dayВҰ379761 of battleВҰ379762.
\v 4 On thatВҰ379774 dayВҰ379766, hisВҰ379793 feetВҰ379765 will standВҰ379764 on the Mt. of Olives, whichВҰ379774 is just east of YerushalemВҰ379778. The Mt. of Olives will be splitВҰ379780 in half between the east and the west by a very greatВҰ379787 valleyВҰ379786, and half of the mountain will go back toward the northВҰ379792 and half toward the southВҰ379795.
\v 5 Then you all will flee down the valley between Yahweh'sВҰ379821 mountains, becauseВҰ379801 the valley between those mountains will reachВҰ379803 to AzelВҰ379809. You will flee just like you fled from the earthquakeВҰ379814 inВҰ379815 the daysВҰ379815 of Yehudah'sВҰ379819 KingВҰ379817 Uzziyah. Then my godВҰ379822 Yahweh will comeВҰ379820 andВҰ379797 all the holy \add >ones\add* will be withВҰ379815 him.
\v 6 On that dayВҰ379829, there'll be no lightВҰ379834вҖ”\add вүҲprecious things will freeze together\add*.
\v 7 On that day (knownВҰ379844 only to YahwehВҰ379845), there'll no longer be day or night, \add вүҲbecause it'll stay lightВҰ379858 at вҖҳnightвҖҷ\add*.
\p
\v 8 On that dayВҰ379862, livingВҰ379867 watersВҰ379865 will flow out of YerushalemВҰ379868. Half of them will flow to the easternВҰ379873 sea and half to the westernВҰ379878 sea, \add both\add* in summerВҰ379879 and in winterВҰ379880.\x + \xo 14:8: \xt Eze 47:1; Yhn 7:38; Rev 22:1.\x*
\v 9 Yahweh will be kingВҰ379885 over all the \add вүҲworld\add*. On that dayВҰ379891 there will \add only\add* be Yahweh, the one GodвҖ”\add вүҲno other gods\add*.
\p
\v 10 All the land will be like the plainВҰ379903 from GebaВҰ379904 to RimmonВҰ379905 southВҰ379906 of Yerushalem. Yerushalem will continue to be \add вүҲin the hills\add* and remainВҰ379909 in its own place, from the BenyaminВҰ379912 Gate to the place where the firstВҰ379917 gate was, to the Corner Gate, and from the Tower of Hanan'el to the king'sВҰ379926 winepressesВҰ379925.
\v 11 It'll be inhabitedВҰ379928 andВҰ379928 never \add completely\add* destroyedВҰ379930 againВҰ379934вҖ”YerushalemВҰ379936 will live inВҰ379929 securityВҰ379937.\x + \xo 14:11: \xt Rev 22:3.\x*
\p
\v 12 The plagueВҰ379942 that YahwehВҰ379945 will use to attack all the nations that fought against YerushalemВҰ379955 will be that their fleshВҰ379958 will rot away even while they're \add still\add* standingВҰ379960 onВҰ379966 their feetВҰ379963. Their eyesВҰ379964 will rot in their socketsВҰ379966 andВҰ379939 their tonguesВҰ379967 will rot in their mouthsВҰ379969.
\p
\v 13 On that dayВҰ379972, YahwehВҰ379977 will \add вүҲcause them to panicВҰ379975\add*вҖ”\add вүҲthey'll grab hold of each other, andВҰ379971 thenВҰ379971 they'll start attacking each other\add*.
\v 14 YehudahВҰ379993 will also fightВҰ379994 against YerushalemВҰ379995, and the wealthВҰ379997 (goldВҰ380002, silverВҰ380003, and clothing) from all the surrounding countriesВҰ380000 will be collectedВҰ379996 \add together\add*.
\p
\v 15 That plague will also be on the horsesВҰ380011 and mulesВҰ380012, the camelsВҰ380013 and donkeysВҰ380014, and on all the other animals inВҰ380020 thoseВҰ380021 campsВҰ380020.
\p
\v 16 \add вүҲAfter that\add*, all who remainВҰ380028 in those nationsВҰ380031 that came against YerushalemВҰ380035 will instead go up from year to year to worshipВҰ380040 the kingВҰ380041 (Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ380042), andВҰ380025 to observe the celebrationВҰ380044 in shelters.\x + \xo 14:16: \xt Lev 23:39-43.\x*
\v 17 It will happen that if anyone from all the countries in the world doesn't goВҰ380054 to YerushalemВҰ380060 to worshipВҰ380061 the kingВҰ380062 (Commander-in-chief Yahweh) thenВҰ380050 Yahweh won'tВҰ380052 \add вүҲsend them any\add* rain.
\v 18 If EgyptВҰ380073 \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add* doesn't go, thenВҰ380070 they won'tВҰ380074 get any rain. A plagueВҰ380082 from YahwehВҰ380085 will attack the nationsВҰ380088 thatВҰ380083 do not go \add вүҲto Yerushalem\add* to observe the celebrationВҰ380092 in shelters.
\v 19 That will be the punishment for EgyptВҰ380101 andВҰ380102 the punishment for every country that doesn't goВҰ380108 to observe that celebrationВҰ380109 in shelters.
\p
\v 20 On that dayВҰ380115, the horses' bellsВҰ380120 will say, вҖң\add вүҲDedicated to\add* Yahweh,вҖқ andВҰ380124 the basins in Yahweh'sВҰ380123 residence will be like the bowlsВҰ380128 in frontВҰ380129 of the altarВҰ380130,
\v 21 because every pot in YerushalemВҰ380136 and YehudahВҰ380137 will be \add вүҲdedicated to\add* Commander-in-chief Yahweh and everyone who brings a sacrificeВҰ380144 will eat from them and boil in them. On that dayВҰ380158, there will no longer be any traders in Commander-in-chief Yahweh'sВҰ380139 residence.
